See how to make kernel headers available to user-space

https://github.com/MarekBykowski/readme/wiki/kernel-headers-for-svc

eg.

* From app dir:
```
rm -rf include_b
mkdir include_b
```

* From kernel dir:
```
make headers_install ARCH=x86 INSTALL_HDR_PATH=/home/mbykowsx/repos/remote-root-complex-emulator/include_b
```

* Test

Makefile:
```
I./include_b/include
make
```

If all is good swap `include` with `include_b/include`.
```
rm -rf include
mv include_b/include .
```

Makefile:
```
I./include
make
```
